On January 29, 1995 about 0811 central standard time, N59556, a Bell 206B3 helicopter, registered to Reeder Flying Service, and operated by Helicopteros SA experienced a hard landing near Neacon, Nicaragua, while on an executive flight to a mining area. 
The flight had originated at an unknown time from an unknown location. 
Any errors in this report will be corrected when the final report has been completed. 
Initial information from the Nicaraguan aviation authorities is that while on final approach the engine failed and the helicopter landed hard. 
This is preliminary information, subject to change, and may contain errors. 
Visual meteorological conditions prevailed and no flight plan was filed for the local flight. 
